  "title": "A Collaborative Approach to Music Therapy Practice in Sensorimotor Rehabilitation",
  "abstract": "Clinical decision making with neurological patients is based on a firm understanding of current theories of motor control in neurological rehabilitation. The music therapy clinician is challenged to integrate these theories with music therapy research and knowledge from clinical practice. Collaboration between therapeutic disciplines in treatment can provide an effective way to integrate multiple perspectives, research knowledge, and practice knowledge in order to best help patients obtain measurable outcomes and maintain/increase independence. Furthermore, the establishment of community-based therapy groups can provide patients with options to maintain rehabilitative work, especially after direct services may become limited due to insurance funding. This article illustrates the implementation of clinical collaboration between neurologic music therapy and physical therapy, bringing inpatient and outpatient adults through a continuum of care to innovative community based services.",
